column1: #Text=is a borough in Gloucester County , New Jersey .
#Text=It is a small quaint little town of a little over 2,500 people .
#Text=Swedesboro was formed as a borough by an Act of the New Jersey Legislature on April 9 , 1902 , from portions of Woolwich Township ( population over 3,000 ) , which completely surrounds it .
#Text=Swedesboro is situated on the south side of Raccoon Creek , about 5 miles from its mouth .
#Text=It is an enclave within Woolwich Township , located 10 miles from Woodbury , NJ and about 18 miles from Camden .
#Text=Swedesboro is one of only two Swedish settlements in New Jersey , along with Bridgeport .

#Text=What is now known as the Borough of Swedesboro , was originally part of the colony named New Sweden , and was made up of Finnish and Swedish settlers [ the present nation of Finland was then a part of Sweden ] .
#Text=From 1638 until 1656 the land along both shores of the Delaware River was the colony 's territory , and ships continued to bring additional settlers , ruled by royal governors .
#Text=Swedesboro is a relatively small town so the best ( and only way if your not in walking distance ) Is by car

#Text=Getting around Swedesboro is actually very simple
#Text=The town is so small that everything is within walking distance .
#Text=Walking from one end of the town to the other would take the average person no more than fifteen minutes .
#Text=Free parking is readily available behind any local retailer or restaurants .
#Text=There is also meter parking available along Country Rd ( the main street of the town ) the cost of the meters is $ .25 every 30 minutes

#Text=This club offers three nine hole courses that are played in three eighteen hole combinations .
#Text=The White Course has open fairways and large greens .
#Text=The Blue Course has tight , tree-lined fairways and fast greens .
#Text=The Red Course has flat fairways and large greens .
#Text=There are water hazards that come into play on all three courses .
